escription\" : \"Spring Cloud Stream Kafka Binder connects Spring Cloud Stream applications to Apache Kafka for message production and consumption. It provides Kafka-specific binder configuration, auto-configuration, metrics, health checks, partitioning, retries, and dead-letter queue support for imperative message channel bindings.\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream/5.0.1/reachability-metadata.json:169:      \"type\" : \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaConnectionDetails\"\nmetadata/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream/5.0.1/reachability-metadata.json:181:      \"type\" : \"org.springframework.cloud.stream.binder.kafka.KafkaBindingRebalanceListener\"\nmetadata/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream/5.0.1/reachability-metadata.json:247:      \"type\" : \"org.springframework.kafka.config.KafkaStreamsCustomizer\"\nmetadata/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Spring Cloud Stream is a framework for building message-driven microservices on Spring Boot using function-based application logic. It provides binding, conversion, partitioning, and lifecycle infrastructure that connects application functions to messaging middleware through binder implementations such as Kafka, RabbitMQ, and Pulsar.\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream-binder-rabbit-core/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Spring Cloud Stream Binder Rabbit Core provides the core classes and configuration properties for integrating Spring Cloud Stream applications with RabbitMQ. It handles RabbitMQ-specific binding, provisioning, and administrative support used by the RabbitMQ binder to map stream destinations to exchanges, queues, and consumer groups.\",\nmetadata/com.github.fd4s/fs2-kafka_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"fs2-kafka is a Scala client library that provides functional, streaming Kafka producers, consumers, and admin clients built on FS2 and Cats Effect. It wraps Apache Kafka clients in composable, resource-safe APIs for publishing, consuming, committing offsets, transactions, serialization, and related Kafka workflows.\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:4:      \"type\": \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaAutoConfiguration\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:28:            \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaConnectionDetails\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:35:            \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaConnectionDetails\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:52:            \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaConnectionDetails\"\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:58:            \"org.springframework.kafka.core.KafkaTemplate\"\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:64:      \"type\": \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaProperties\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:70:      \"type\": \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaProperties$Admin\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:76:      \"type\": \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaProperties$Cleanup\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:82:      \"type\": \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaProperties$Consumer\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:88:      \"type\": \"org.springframework.boot.kafka.autoconfigure.KafkaProperties$IsolationLevel\",\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-kafka/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:94:      \"type\